         <abstract>
            <p>An interpolation algorithm is derived, which will construct an (n + 1)-point interpolant based on any sequence of interpolatory functions that can be defined by a three-term linear recursion. By suitable parameter choice, a single algorithm can be made to interpolate in terms of the classical polynomial sequences or in terms of trigonometric or hyperbolic series etc. An analysis of truncation error is included.</p>
          </abstract>
